.TH XmTextSetString 3X "" "" "" "OSF/Motif"
.SH NAME
\*LXmTextSetString\*O \- A Text function that sets the string value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sS
.iS
\&#include <Xm/Text.h>
.sp \n(PDu
void XmTextSetString (\*Vwidget, value\*L)
.ta .5i 1.5i
	Widget	\*Vwidget\*L;
	char	\*V* value\*L;
.wH .fi
.ne 12
.iE
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "XmTextSetString"
.iX "Text functions" "XmTextSetString"
\*LXmTextSetString\*O sets the string value of the Text widget.
This routine calls the widget's \*LXmNvalueChangedCallback\*O and
verification callbacks, either \*LXmNmodifyVerifyCallback\*O or
\*LXmNmodifyVerifyCallbackWcs\*O, or both.  If both verification
callback lists are registered, the procedures of the
\*LXmNmodifyVerifyCallback\*O list are executed first and the resulting
data is passed to the \*LXmNmodifyVerifyCallbackWcs\*O callbacks.
It also sets the insertion cursor position to the beginning of the
string and calls the widget's \*LXmNmotionVerifyCallback\*O callbacks.
.VL .75i 
.LI "\*Vwidget\*O"
Specifies the Text widget ID
.LI "\*Vvalue\*O"
Specifies the character pointer to the string value and places the
string into the text edit window
.LE 
.PP 
For a complete definition of Text and its associated resources, see
\*LXmText(3X)\*O.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.na
\*LXmText(3X)\*O and
\*LXmTextSetStringWcs(3X)\*O.
.ad
.EQ
delim off
.EN
